crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This code implements a framework for defining and manipulating network protocol packets. It uses a metaclass to dynamically generate getter and setter methods, along with properties, for various data fields (bits, bytes, words, longs, and three-byte values) within a packet header. These fields are defined using specialized classes that inherit from a base `Field` class. The framework integrates with the `impacket` library to provide structured access and modification capabilities for underlying packet data buffers.
